ew In Article|Cross Reference\n\n23.: Rona K.A., Reynolds J., Schwameis K., et al.: Efficacy of magnetic sphincter augmentation in patients with large hiatal hernias . Surg Endosc 2017; 31 (5): pp. 2096-2102.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n24.: Buckley FP 3rd, Bell R.C.W., Freeman K., Doggett S., Heidrick R.: Favorable results from a prospective evaluation of 200 patients with large hiatal hernias undergoing LINX magnetic sphincter augmentation . Surg Endosc 2018; 32 (4): pp. 1762-1768.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n25.: Tatum J.M., Alicuben E., Bildzukewicz N., Samakar K., Houghton C.C., Lipham J.C.: Minimal versus obligatory dissection of the diaphragmatic hiatus during magnetic sphincter augmentation surgery . Surg Endosc 2019; 33 (3): pp. 782-788.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n26.: Pandolfino J.E., Kim H., Ghosh S.K., Clarke J.O., Zhang Q., Kahrilas P.J.: High-resolution manometry of the EGJ: an analysis of crural diaphragm function in GERD . Am J Gastroenterol 2007; 102 (5): pp. 1056-1063.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n27.: Louie B.E., Kapur S., Blitz M., Farivar A.S., Valli\u00e8res E., Aye R.W.: Length and pressure of the reconstructed lower esophageal sphincter is determined by both crural closure and Nissen fundoplication . J Gastrointest Surg 2013; 17 (2): pp. 236-243.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n28.: Irribarra M.M., Blitz S., Wilshire C.L., et al.: Does treatment of the hiatus influence the outcomes of magnetic sphincter augmentation for chronic GERD? . J Gastrointest Surg 2019; 23 (6): pp. 1104-1112.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n29.: Leeds S.G., Ward M.A.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation: poor consensus among experts regarding key technical aspects of implantation . Surg Laparosc Endosc Percutan Tech 2020; 31 (1): pp. 36-39. Published 2020 Aug 5 .\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n30.: Ayazi S., Chowdhury N., Zaidi A.H., et al.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation (MSA) in patients with hiatal hernia: clinical outcome and patterns of recurrence . Surg Endosc 2020; 34 (4): pp. 1835-1846.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n31.: Skubleny D., Switzer N.J., Dang J., et al.: LINX\u00ae magnetic esophageal sphincter augmentation versus Nissen fundoplication for gastroesophageal reflux disease: a systematic review and meta-analysis . Surg Endosc 2017; 31 (8): pp. 3078-3084.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n32.: Aiolfi A., Asti E., Bernardi D., et al.: Early results of magnetic sphincter augmentation versus fundoplication for gastroesophageal reflux disease: systematic review and meta-analysis . Int J Surg 2018; 52: pp. 82-88.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n33.: Asti E., Milito P., Froiio C., Milani V., Bonavina L.: Comparative outcomes of Toupet fundoplication and magnetic sphincter augmentation . Dis Esophagus 2023; 36 (suppl 1):\n\nView In Article\n\n34.: Callahan Z.M., Amundson J., Su B., Kuchta K., Ujiki M.: Outcomes after anti-reflux procedures: Nissen, Toupet, magnetic sphincter augmentation or anti-reflux mucosectomy? . Surg Endosc 2023; 37 (5): pp. 3944-3951.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n35.: Huynh P., Konda V., Sanguansataya S., Ward M.A., Leeds S.G.: Mind the gap: current treatment alternatives for GERD patients failing medical treatment and not ready for a fundoplication . Surg Laparosc Endosc Percutan Tech 2020; 31 (2): pp. 264-276. Published 2020 Dec 16 .\n\nView In Article\n\n36.: Bell R., Lipham J., Louie B., et al.: Laparoscopic magnetic sphincter augmentation versus double-dose proton pump inhibitors for management of moderate-to-severe regurgitation in GERD: a randomized controlled trial . Gastrointest Endosc 2019; 89 (1): pp. 14-22.e1.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n37.: Desart K., Rossidis G., Michel M., Lux T., Ben-David K.: Gastroesophageal reflux management with the LINX\u00ae system for gastroesophageal reflux disease following laparoscopic sleeve gastrectomy . J Gastrointest Surg 2015; 19 (10): pp. 1782-1786.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n38.: Kuckelman J.P., Phillips C.J., Derickson M.J., Faler B.J., Martin M.J.: Esophageal magnetic sphincter augmentation as a novel approach to post-bariatric surgery gastroesophageal reflux disease . Obes Surg 2018; 28 (10): pp. 3080-3086.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n39.: Leeds S.G., Ngov A., O Ogola G., Ward M.A.: Safety of magnetic sphincter augmentation in patients with prior bariatric and anti-reflux surgery . Surg Endosc 2021; 35 (9): pp. 5322-5327.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n40.: Bellorin O., Dolan P., Vigiola-Cruz M., et al.: Robotic-assisted approaches to GERD following sleeve gastrectomy . Surg Endosc 2021; 35 (6): pp. 3033-3039.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n41.: Patel S.H., Smith B., Polak R., Pomeranz M., Patel P.V., Englehardt R.: Laparoscopic magnetic sphincter augmentation device placement for patients with medically-refractory gastroesophageal reflux after sleeve gastrectomy . Surg Endosc 2022; 36 (11): pp. 8255-8260.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n42.: Khaitan L., Hill M., Michel M., et al.: Feasibility and efficacy of magnetic sphincter augmentation for the management of gastroesophageal reflux disease post-sleeve gastrectomy for obesity . Obes Surg 2023; 33 (1): pp. 387-396.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n43.: Ward M.A., Ebrahim A., Kopita J., et al.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation is an effective treatment for atypical symptoms caused by gastroesophageal reflux disease . Surg Endosc 2020; 34 (11): pp. 4909-4915.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n44.: Smoot M., Ward M.A., Arviso L., Sanchez C.E., Leeds S.G.: Hiatal hernia repair and magnetic sphincter augmentation to treat laryngopharyngeal reflux aiding the prevention of recurrent laryngeal cancer . Proc (Bayl Univ Med Cent). 2020; 34 (1): pp. 148-150. Published 2020 Sep 28 .\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n45.: Kellokumpu I., Voutilainen M., Haglund C., F\u00e4rkkil\u00e4 M., Roberts P.J., Kautiainen H.: Quality of life following laparoscopic Nissen fundoplication: assessing short-term and long-term outcomes . World J Gastroenterol 2013; 19 (24): pp. 3810-3818.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n46.: Bonavina L., Saino G., Bona D., Sironi A., Lazzari V.: One hundred consecutive patients treated with magnetic sphincter augmentation for gastroesophageal reflux disease: 6 years of clinical experience from a single center . J Am Coll Surg 2013; 217 (4): pp. 577-585.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n47.: Saino G., Bonavina L., Lipham J.C., Dunn D., Ganz R.A.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation for gastroesophageal reflux at 5 Years: final results of a pilot study show long-term acid reduction and symptom improvement . J Laparoendosc Adv Surg Tech 2015; 25 (10): pp. 787-792.\n\nView In Article\n\n48.: Ferrari D., Asti E., Lazzari V., Siboni S., Bernardi D., Bonavina L.: Six to 12-year outcomes of magnetic sphincter augmentation for gastroesophageal reflux disease . Sci Rep 2020; 10 (1): Published 2020 Aug 13 .\n\nView In Article\n\n49.: Bonavina L., Horbach T., Schoppmann S.F., DeMarchi J.: Three-year clinical experience with magnetic sphincter augmentation and laparoscopic fundoplication . Surg Endosc 2021; 35 (7): pp. 3449-3458.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n50.: Dunn C.P., Zhao J., Wang J.C., et al.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation with hiatal hernia repair: long term outcomes . Surg Endosc 2021; 35 (10): pp. 5607-5612.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n51.: Leeds S.G., Ebrahim A., Potter E.M., et al.: The role of preoperative workup in predicting dysphagia, dilation, or explantation after magnetic sphincter augmentation . Surg Endosc 2020; 34 (8): pp. 3663-3668.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n52.: Ayazi S., Zheng P., Zaidi A.H., et al.: Magnetic sphincter augmentation and postoperative dysphagia: characterization, clinical risk factors, and management . J Gastrointest Surg 2020; 24 (1): pp. 39-49.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n53.: Tatum J.M., Alicuben E., Bildzukewicz N., Samakar K., Houghton C.C., Lipham J.C.: Removing the magnetic sphincter augmentation device: operative management and outcomes . Surg Endosc 2019; 33 (8): pp. 2663-2669.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n54.: DeMarchi J., Schwiers M., Soberman M., Tokarski A.: Evolution of a novel technology for gastroesophageal reflux disease: a safety perspective of magnetic sphincter augmentation . Dis Esophagus 2021; 34 (11):\n\nView In Article\n\n55.: Lipham J.C., Taiganides P.A., Louie B.E., Ganz R.A., DeMeester T.R.: Safety analysis of first 1000 patients treated with magnetic sphincter augmentation for gastroesophageal reflux disease . Dis Esophagus 2015; 28 (4): pp. 305-311.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n56.: Smith C.D., Ganz R.A., Lipham J.C., Bell R.C., Rattner D.W.: Lower esophageal sphincter augmentation for gastroesophageal reflux disease: the safety of a modern implant . J Laparoendosc Adv Surg Tech 2017; 27 (6): pp. 586-591.\n\nView In Article\n\n57.: Tatum J.M., Alicuben E., Bildzukewicz N., Samakar K., Houghton C.C., Lipham J.C.: Removing the magnetic sphincter augmentation device: operative management and outcomes . Surg Endosc 2019; 33 (8): pp. 2663-2669.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n58.: Chandan S., Mohan B.P., Khan S.R., et al.: Clinical efficacy and safety of magnetic sphincter augmentation (MSA) and transoral incisionless fundoplication (TIF2) in refractory gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD): a systematic review and meta-analysis . Endosc Int Open 2021; 9 (4): pp. E583-E598.\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 by Elsevier Inc. All rights are reserved, including those for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies.\n\n## Get rights and content\u00a0\n\n##\n\n281240\n\n  - Google Play - Go to our Google Play page\n  - Apple App Store - Go to our A