ion of long-term outcomes . Surg Endosc 2007; 21 (11): pp. 1978-1984.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n15.: Perez A.R., Moncure A.C., Rattner D.W.: Obesity adversely affects the outcome of antireflux operations . Surg Endosc 2001; 15 (9): pp. 986-989.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n16.: Akimoto S., et al.: Association of body mass index (BMI) with patterns of fundoplication failure: insights gained . J Gastrointest Surg 2015; 19 (11): pp. 1943-1948.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n17.: Bhayani N.H., et al.: End of the road for a dysfunctional end organ: laparoscopic gastrectomy for refractory gastroparesis . J Gastrointest Surg 2015; 19 (3): pp. 411-417.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n18.: Masclee G.M.C., et al.: Systematic review on sleeve gastrectomy or Roux-en-Y gastric bypass surgery for refractory gastroparesis . Surg Obes Relat Dis 2023; 19 (3): pp. 253-264.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n19.: Landreneau J.P., et al.: Gastrectomy versus stomach left in situ with Roux-en-Y reconstruction for the treatment of gastroparesis . Surg Endosc 2020; 34 (4): pp. 1847-1855.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n20.: Lu D., et al.: Investigating rates of reoperation or postsurgical gastroparesis following fundoplication or paraesophageal hernia repair in New York State . Surg Endosc 2019; 33 (9): pp. 2886-2894.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n21.: Pasricha P.J., et al.: Outcomes and factors associated with reduced symptoms in patients with gastroparesis . Gastroenterology 2015; 149 (7): pp. 1762-1774.e4.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n22.: Robertson J.P., Van der Wall H., Falk G.L.: Failed fundoplication with delayed gastric emptying: efficacy of subtotal gastrectomy . ANZ J Surg 2022; 92 (4): pp. 764-768.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 by Else