 al.: Endoscopic mucosal incision and muscle interruption (MIMI) for the treatment of Zenker\u2019s diverticulum . Surg Endosc 2021; 35 (7): pp. 3896-3904.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n109.: Al Ghamdi S.S., Farha J., Moran R.A., et al.: Zenker\u2019s peroral endoscopic myotomy, or flexible or rigid septotomy for Zenker\u2019s diverticulum: a multicenter retrospective comparison . Endoscopy 2022; 54 (4): pp. 345-351.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n110.: Budnicka A., Januszewicz W., Bia\u0142ek A.B., Spychalski M., Regu\u0142a J., Kaminski M.F.: Peroral endoscopic myotomy in the management of Zenker\u2019s diverticulum: a retrospective multicenter study . J Clin Med 2021; 10 (2): pp. 187.\n\nView In Article\n\n111.: Elkholy S., El-Sherbiny M., Delano-Alonso R., et al.: Peroral endoscopic myotomy as treatment for Zenker\u2019s diverticulum (Z-POEM): a multi-center international study . Esophagus 2021; 18 (3): pp. 693-699.\n\nView In Article\n\n112.: Kahaleh M., Mahpour N.Y., Tyberg A., et al.: Per oral endoscopic myotomy for Zenker\u2019s diverticulum: a novel and superior technique compared with septotomy? . J Clin Gastroenterol 2022; 56 (3): pp. 224-227.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 by Elsevier Inc. All rights are reserved, including those for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies.\n\n## Get rights and content\u00a0\n\n##\n\n281240\n\n  - Google Play - Go to our Google Play page\n  - Apple App Store - Go to our Apple App Store page\n  - Facebook - Go to our Facebook page\n  - LinkedIn - Go to our LinkedIn page\n  - X - Go to our X page\n\nElsevier (opens in a new window)\n\n  - Contact Us (opens in a new window)\n  - Resource Center (opens in a new window)\n  - Registered User Agreement (opens in a new window)\n  - Help (opens in a new window)\