 oncology . J Natl Compr Cancer Netw 2019; 17 (7): pp. 855-883.\n\nView In Article\n\n21.: Catalano M.F., Van Dam J., Sivak M.V.: Malignant esophageal strictures: staging accuracy of endoscopic ultrasonography . Gastrointest Endosc 1995; 41 (6): pp. 535-539.\n\nView In Article\n\n22.: Wallace M.B., Hawes R.H., Sahai A.V., Van Velse A., Hoffman B.J.: Dilation of malignant esophageal stenosis to allow EUS guided fine-needle aspiration: safety and effect on patient management . Gastrointest Endosc 2000; 51 (3): pp. 309-313.\n\nView In Article\n\n23.: Nesje L.B., Svanes K., Viste A., Laerum O.D., Odegaard S.: Comparison of a linear miniature ultrasound probe and a radial-scanning echoendoscope in TN staging of esophageal cancer . Scand J Gastroenterol 2000; 35 (9): pp. 997-1002.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n24.: Worrell S.G., Oh D.S., Greene C.L., Demeester S.R., Hagen J.A.: Endoscopic ultrasound staging of stenotic esophageal cancers may be unnecessary to determine the need for neoadjuvant therapy . J Gastrointest Surg 2014; 18 (2): pp. 318-320.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n25.: Endoscopic ultrasound restating after neoadjuvant chemotherapy in esophageal cancer, first author Afonso Ribeiro . Am J Gastroenterol 2006;\n\nView In Article\n\n26.: Beseth B.D., Bedford R., Isacoff W.H.: Endoscopic ultrasound does not accurately assess pathologic stage of esophageal cancer after neoadjuvant chemoradiotherapy . Am Surg 2000; 66 (9): pp. 827-831.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 by Elsevier Inc. All rights are reserved, including those for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies.\n\n## Get rights and content\u00a0\n\n##\n\n281240\n\n  - Google Play - Go to our Google Play page\n  - Apple App Store - Go to our Apple App Store page\n  - Facebook - Go to our Fac