ce\n\n45.: Mishra B., Madhusudhan K.S., Kilambi R., Das P., Pal S., Srivastava D.N.: Malignant schwannoma of the esophagus: a rare case report . Korean J Thorac Cardiovasc Surg 2016; 49 (1): pp. 63-66.\n\nView In Article\n\n46.: Giacobbe A., Facciorusso D., Conoscitore P., Spirito F., Squillante M.M., Bisceglia M.: Granular cell tumor of the esophagus . Am J Gastroenterol 1988; 83 (12): pp. 1398-1400.\n\nView In Article\n\n47.: Sarma D.P., Rodriguez F.H., Deiparine E.M., Weilbaecher T.G.: Symptomatic granular cell tumor of the esophagus . J Surg Oncol 1986; 33 (4): pp. 246-249.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n48.: Subramanyam K., Shannon C.R., Patterson M., Davis M., Gourley W.K.: Granular cell myoblastoma of the esophagus . J Clin Gastroenterol 1984; 6 (2): pp. 113-118.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n49.: Kahng D.H., Kim G.H., Park D.Y., et al.: Endoscopic resection of granular cell tumors in the gastrointestinal tract: a single center experience . Surg Endosc 2013; 27 (9): pp. 3228-3236.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n50.: Coutinho D.S., Soga J., Yoshikawa T., et al.: Granular cell tumors of the esophagus: a report of two cases and review of the literature . Am J Gastroenterol 1985; 80 (10): pp. 758-762.\n\nView In Article\n\n51.: Shi Y., Chai N., Zhong L., et al.: Experience with esophageal granular cell tumors: clinical and endoscopic analysis of 22 cases . Dig Dis Sci 2021; 66 (4): pp. 1233-1239.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n52.: Tada S., Iida M., Yao T., Miyagahara T., Hasuda S., Fujishima M.: Granular cell tumor of the esophagus: endoscopic ultrasonographic demonstration and endoscopic removal . Am J Gastroenterol 1990; 85 (11): pp. 1507-1511.\n\nView In Article\n\n53.: Reed C.E.: Benign tumors of the esophagus . Chest Surg Clin 1994; 4 (4): pp. 769-783.\n\nView In Article\n\n54.: Mineo T.C., Biancari F., Francioni F., Trentino P., Casciani C.U.: Conservative approach to granular cell tumour of the oesophagus. Three case reports .