rediction of bleeding and stricture formation after corrosive ingestion by EUS concurrent with upper endoscopy . Gastrointest Endosc 2004; 60 (5): pp. 827-833.\n\nView In Article\n\n22.: Bonnici K.S., Wood D.M., Dargan P.I.: Should computerised tomography replace endoscopy in the evaluation of symptomatic ingestion of corrosive substances? . Clin Toxicol (Phila) 2014; 52 (9): pp. 911-925.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n23.: Methasate A., Lohsiriwat V.: Role of endoscopy in caustic injury of the esophagus . World J Gastrointest Endosc 2018; 10 (10): pp. 274-282.\n\nView In Article\n\n24.: Zargar S.A., Kochhar R., Mehta SMehta S.K.: The role of fiberoptic endoscopy in the management of corrosive ingestion and modified endoscopic classification of burns . Gastrointest Endosc 1991; 37 (2): pp. 165-169.\n\nView In Article\n\n25.: Boskovic A., Stankovic I.: Predictability of gastroesophageal caustic injury from clinical findings: is endoscopy mandatory in children? . Eur J Gastroenterol Hepatol 2014; 26 (5): pp. 499-503.\n\nView In Article\n\n26.: Temiz A., Oguzkurt P., Ezer S.S., Ince E., Hicsonmez A.: Predictability of outcome of caustic ingestion by esophagogastroduodenoscopy in children . World J Gastroenterol 2012; 18 (10): pp. 1098-1103.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n27.: Kamijo Y., Kondo I., Kokuto M., Kataoka Y., Soma K.: Miniprobe ultrasonography for determining prognosis in corrosive esophagitis . Am J Gastroenterol 2004; 99 (5): pp. 851-854.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n28.: KayM W.R.: Caustic ingestions in children . Curr Opin Pediatr 2009; 21 (5): pp. 651-654.\n\nView In Article\n\n29.: De Lusong M.A.A., Timbol A.B.G., Tuazon D.J.S.: Management of esophageal caustic injury . World J Gastrointest Pharmacol Ther 2017; 8 (2): pp. 90-98.\n\nView In Article\n\n30.: Obarski P., W\u0142odarczyk J.: Diagnosis and management of gastrointestinal chemical burns and post-burn oesophageal stenosis . Polish J Cardio-Thorac Surg 2021; 18 (4): pp. 252-259.\n\nView In Article\n\n31.: Usta M., Erkan T., Cokugras F.C., et al.: High doses of methylprednisolone in the management of caustic esophageal burns . Pediatr 2014; 133 (6): pp. E1518-E1524.\n\nView In Article\n\n32.: Anderson K.D., Rouse TMRandolph J.G.: A controlled trial of corticosteroids in children with corrosive injury of the esophagus . N Engl J Med 1990; 323 (10): pp. 637-640.\n\nView In Article\n\n33.: Cakal B., Akbal E., K\u00f6kl\u00fc S., Babal\u0131 A., Ko\u00e7ak E., Ta\u015f A.: Acute therapy with intravenous omeprazole on caustic esophageal injury: a prospective case series . Dis Esophaugs 2013; 26 (1): pp. 22-26.\n\nView In Article\n\n34.: Javed A., Pal S., Dash N.R., Sahni P., Chattopadhyay T.K.: Outcome following surgical management of corrosive strictures of the esophagus . Ann Surg 2011; 254 (1): pp. 62-66.\n\nView In Article\n\n35.: Katz A., Kluger Y.: Caustic material ingestion injuries-paradigm shift in diagnosis and treatment . Health Care Curr Rev 2015; 3: pp. 1-4.\n\nView In Article\n\n36.: Kochhar R., Ray J.D., Sriram P.V., Kumar S., Singh K.: Intralesional steroids augment the effects of endoscopic dilation in corrosive esophageal strictures . Gastrointest Endosc 1999; 49 (4 Pt 1): pp. 509-513.\n\nView In Article\n\n37.: Nijhawan S., Udawat H.P., Nagar P.: Aggressive bougie dilatation and intralesional steroids is effective in refractory benign esophageal strictures secondary to corrosive ingestion . Dis Esophaugs 2016; 29 (8): pp. 1027-1031.\n\nView In Article\n\n38.: Uhlen S., Fayoux P., Vachin F., et al.: Mitomycin C: an alternative conservative treatment for refractory esophageal stricture in children? . Endoscopy 2006; 38 (4): pp. 404-407.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n39.: El-Asmar K.M., Hassan M.A., Abdelkader H.M., Hamza A.F.: Topical mitomycin C can effectively alleviate dysphagia in children with long-segment caustic esophageal strictures . Dis Esophaugs 2015; 28 (5): pp. 422-427.\n\nView In Article\n\n40.: Rosseneu S., Afzal N., Yerushalmi B., et al.: Topical application of mitomycin-C in oesophageal strictures . J Pediatr Gastroenterol Nutr 2007; 44 (3): pp. 336-341.\n\nView In Article\n\n41.: Broto J., Asensio M., Vernet J.M.: Results of a new technique in the treatment of severe esophageal stenosis in children: poliflex stents . J Pediatr Gastroenterol Nutr 2003; 37 (2): pp. 203-206.\n\nView In Article\n\n42.: Atabek C., Surer I., Demirbag S., Caliskan B., Ozturk H., Cetinkursun S.: Increasing tendency in caustic esophageal burns and long-term polytetrafluorethylene stenting in severe cases: 10 years experience . J Pediatr Surg 2007; 42 (4): pp. 636-640.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n43.: Gupta N.M., Gupta R.: Transhiatal esophageal resection for corrosive injury . Ann Surg 2004; 239 (3): pp. 359-363.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n44.: Knezevi\u0107 J.D., Radovanovi\u0107 N.S., Simi\u0107 A.P., et al.: Colon interposition in the treatment of esophageal caustic strictures: 40 years of experience . Dis Esophagus 2007; 20 (6): pp. 530-534.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n45.: Gerzic Z.B., Knezevic J.B., Milicevic M.N., Jovanovic B.K.: Esophagocoloplasty in the management of postcorrosive strictures of the esophagus . Ann Surg 1990; 211 (3): pp. 329-336.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 by Elsevier Inc. All rights are reserved, including those for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies.\n\n## Get rights and content\u00a0\n\n##\n\n281240\n\n  - Google Play - Go to our Google Play page\n  - Apple App Store - Go to our Apple App Store page\n  - Facebook - Go to our Facebook page\n  - LinkedIn - Go to our LinkedIn page\n  - X - Go to our X page\n\nElsevier (opens in a new window)\n\n  - Contact Us (opens in a new window)\n  - Resource Center (opens in a n