View In Article|Cross Reference\n\n84.: Businello G., Dal Pozzo C.A., Sbaraglia M., et al.: Histopathological landscape of rare oesophageal neoplasms . World J Gastroenterol 2020; 26 (27): pp. 3865-3888.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n85.: Lewis R.B., Mehrotra A.K., Rodriguez P., Levine M.S.: From the radiologic pathology archives: esophageal neoplasms: radiologic-pathologic correlation . Radiographics 2013; 33 (4): pp. 1083-1108.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n86.: Ha C., Regan J., Cetindag I.B., Ali A., Mellinger J.D.: Benign esophageal tumors . Surg Clin North Am 2015; 95 (3): pp. 491-514.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n87.: Sun X., Niwa T., Ozawa S., Endo J., Hashimoto J.: Detecting lymph node metastasis of esophageal cancer on dual-energy computed tomography . Acta Radiol 2022; 63 (1): pp. 3-10.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n88.: Cheng F., Liu Y., Du L., et al.: Evaluation of optimal monoenergetic images acquired by dual-energy CT in the diagnosis of T staging of thoracic esophageal cancer . Insights Imaging 2023; 14 (1): pp. 33. Published 2023 Feb 10 .\n\nView In Article\n\n89.: Schwartz F.R., Samei E., Marin D.: Exploiting the potential of photon-counting CT in abdominal imaging . Invest Radiol 2023; 58 (7): pp. 488-498.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n90.: Shi Z., Zhang Z., Liu Z., et al.: Methodological quality of machine learning-based quantitative imaging analysis studies in esophageal cancer: a systematic review of clinical outcome prediction after concurrent chemoradiotherapy . Eur J Nucl Med Mol Imaging 2022; 49 (8): pp. 2462-2481.\n\nView In Article|Cross Reference\n\n91.: Zhang P., She Y., Gao J., et al.: Development of a deep learning system to detect esophageal cancer by barium esophagram . Front Oncol 2022; 12: Published 2022 Jun 21 .\n\nView In Article\n\nPrevious ChapterGo to the previous chapter\n\nNext ChapterGo to the next chapter\n\n\n\n## Shackelford''s Surgery of the Alimentary Tract\n\nNinth Edition\n\nC